http://www.thehindu.com/news/cities/Visakhapatnam/BHEL-commissions-520-MW-unit-of-HNPCL/article13995658.ece

Hinduja National Power Company Limited (HNPCL) achieved a significant milestone on Monday with Bharat Heavy Electricals Limited (BHEL) successfully commissioning the 520 MW coal-based thermal generating unit.The unit at Palavalasa near here has been commissioned after the project suffered huge loss due to Hudhud.Significantly, in Visakhapatnam district, four 500 MW thermal sets supplied and executed by BHEL are already in successful operation at Simhadri Super Thermal Power Station of the NTPC.The 2x520 MW HNPCL is being executed by BHEL on EPC (Engineering, Procurement and Construction) basis.This project is located on the coast of the Bay of Bengal using single flow condenser and sea water as main cooling water.